briefdescription.para: Destructively destroys all nodes in the graph.
Add a node to this graph.

detaileddescription.para: The node will get added to this graph. It is not automatically connected to anything, any connections will need to be made manually after the node is added. The graph takes ownership of the Node.

briefdescription.para: Removes a Node from the graph BUT doesn't destroy it. Ownership is passed to new_parent.
Retrieve a complete list of the nodes belonging to this graph.
Returns whether a certain Node is in the graph or not.
Signal emitted when a Node is added to the graph.
Signal emitted when a Node is removed from the graph.
Signal emitted when a member node of this graph has been connected to another (creating an "edge")
Signal emitted when a member node of this graph has been disconnected from another (removing an "edge")
The main timeline object, an graph of edited clips that forms a complete edit.
